What is Cross-Zone Load Balancing?
Cross-Zone Load Balancing is a setting on AWS Load Balancers that allows traffic to be distributed evenly across
ALL registered EC2 instances in ALL Availability Zones — regardless of which AZ the traffic originally entered through.

Step 1 — Navigate: Go to AWS Console → EC2
       In the left panel → Click "Load Balancers"
       Select ELB-Demo-NLB
Step 2 — Go to Attributes:
       Click the "Attributes" tab
       Click "Edit"(top right)
Step 3 — Enable Cross-Zone:
       Setting	              Value
       Cross-Zone Load Balancing	Turn ON ✅
       Click "Save Changes" ✅
⏳ Takes effect immediately — no restart required.

Load Balancer	       Default	              Can Change?
ALB	              ✅ Always ON	              ❌ Cannot disable
NLB	              ❌ OFF by default	       ✅ Can enable
GLB	              ❌ OFF by default	       ✅ Can enable
CLB	              ❌ OFF by default	       ✅ Can enable

